'''聖阿方索渡假村'''（{{lang-es|'''San Alfonso del Mar''' }}），是一座位於[[智利|智利]]首都[[聖地亞哥-德智利|聖地亞哥]]西邊約{{convert|100|km}}的城市[[阿爾加羅沃_(智利)|阿爾加羅沃]]中<ref name="ngbig"/>。度假村擁有一座[[金氏世界紀錄|金氏世界紀錄]]認證的世界最大[[游泳池|游泳池]]<ref name="ngbig">{{cite news | title=Big Dipper | work=National Geographic | date=April 2010 | page=30}}</ref><ref name="rec">{{cite web| title=Largest swimming pool by area| url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/1/largest-swimming-pool-by-area| work=Guinness World Records| accessdate=25 May 2012| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107020301/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/1/largest-swimming-pool-by-area| archive-date=2014-01-07| dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

游泳池長約{{convert|1.013|km|mi}}<ref name="rec"/>，占地約{{convert|8|ha|acre}}<ref name="rec" />，容量約{{convert|250000000|l|impgal}}<ref name="snopes">{{cite web | author= Barbara Mikkelson; David P. Mikkelson |title=Pool Queue: Worlds Largest Swimming Pool | work=Snopes | url=http://www.snopes.com/photos/architecture/largestpool.asp | accessdate=28 October 2012}}</ref>，最大深度為{{convert|3.5|m}}.<ref name="snopes" /><ref name="deep">{{cite news | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-509718/Try-making-splash-worlds-largest-swimming-pool--1-000-yards-long.html | title=The Making Splash World's Largest Swimming Pool 1,000 yards long | work=The  Daily Mail | accessdate=27 October 2012 | archive-date=2018-08-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810200837/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-509718/Try-making-splash-worlds-largest-swimming-pool--1-000-yards-long.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，池水抽取自[[太平洋|太平洋]]的海水，經處理過濾後注入泳池。並有能加熱九度的恆溫溫水設施，使得智利海域冰冷的深層海水得以變得舒適。

==開發==
泳池由開發商[[Fernando_Fischmann|Fernando Fischmann]]的智利公司：「水晶潟湖」所建造，於2006年12月開放。早期單是游泳池的過濾系統建造經費，就花費約350萬美元<ref name="dmar">{{cite news | author= | title=World's Largest Swimming Pool San Alfonso del Mar | url=http://www.explorra.com/attractions/world-largest-swimming-pool-san-alfonso-del-mar_11595 | work=Explorra | date= | accessdate=28 October 2012 | archive-date=2014-04-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407184115/http://www.explorra.com/attractions/world-largest-swimming-pool-san-alfonso-del-mar_11595 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="ngblog">{{cite news | author=Janelle Nanos | date=22 March 2010 | title=Today Pic The World's Largest | url=http://blogs.nationalgeographic.com/blogs/intelligenttravel/2010/03/todays-pic-the-worlds-largest.html | work=National Geographic Blogs | accessdate=28 October 2012 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103205920/http://blogs.nationalgeographic.com/blogs/intelligenttravel/2010/03/todays-pic-the-worlds-largest.html | archivedate=2012年11月3日 }}</ref>，全區建設經費則高達15億至20億美元，並且每年須投入將近400萬美元的維護費用<ref>{{cite news | author=Daniel Lim | title=World’s Largest Swimming Pool cost nearly Two Billion Dollars to Build | url=http://www.slashgear.com/worlds-largest-swimming-pool-cost-nearly-two-billion-dollars-to-build-229828/ | work=Slash Gear | date=22 January 2008 | accessdate=29 October 2012 | archive-date=2017-08-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821090017/https://www.slashgear.com/worlds-largest-swimming-pool-cost-nearly-two-billion-dollars-to-build-229828/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author=Spooky | title=World’s largest swimming pool | url=http://www.odditycentral.com/pics/worlds-largest-swimming-pool.html | work=Oddity Central | date=2 March 2008 | accessdate=28 October 2012 | archive-date=2014-07-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714171459/http://www.odditycentral.com/pics/worlds-largest-swimming-pool.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="snopes"/>。

